span>I love the part about neuroticism and physical vulnerability. When we =
become mothers, our sense of physical vulnerability extends to the vulnerab=
ility of our children. When my son was first born -premature, 5 lbs - I was=
 in a state of constant terror (I was neurotic before, and that just threw =
gas on the flames) I used to imagine all the ways I could protect him if so=
meone broke into our Tenderloin SRO and tried to harm him. I was nuts. But =
